                     <interp inst="def1-827-18390204" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN SAWYER</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390204-827-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390204-827-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390204-827-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390204-cd-252" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-827-offence-1 t18390204-cd-252"></join>15th of January</rs>, 1 pair of boots, value 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. the goods of <persName id="t18390204-name-1570" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1570" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1570" type="surname" value="ESTERFORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1570" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-827-offence-1 t18390204-name-1570"></join>John Esterford</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1571" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1571" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1571" type="surname" value="ESTERFORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1571" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN ESTERFORD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shoemaker, and live at Royal Hill, Green<lb></lb>wich. The prisoner was in my employ in the beginning of January—I missed boots and shoes; and one day I missed a pair while he was waiting for his work, and found them in his basket, as he was going out of the shop with them—I found another pair of my boots at the pawnbroker's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was any thing said about your overlooking it if he confessed? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I said I would overlook about the shoes—the boots were taken first—I have given him work for a year and a half—he calls at the shop for it, and goes away with it—I am quite certain I did not give him these boots to make—I never gave him more than two pairs to make at once—these boots were all ready for sale—they did not want any thing done to them—I did not give them to him as a pattern to make others by—I may have done such a thing, but I never gave him these—I saw them hanging on the door-post before he came into the shop, and when he was gone I missed them—he promised to give me the duplicates of these boots—he gave me one, but I could not find the other.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1572" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1572" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1572" type="surname" value="LEVICK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1572" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LEVICK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Nash, a pawnbroker, at Green<lb></lb>wich. On the 15th of January the prisoner pawned these boots for 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he looked like a shoemaker, and they often pledge work.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to.</hi>)</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
